condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Disbursement Condition: Schedule 2, Section I.A, paragraph 2 (b) | Description :The Borrower, through MPW,shall: (b) by no later than November in each calendar year of Project implementation, commencing on November 30, 2012, identifyeach Participating Kecamatan, Participating Kota, Participating Kabupaten and Participating Kelurahan, in each case in accordancewith the Project Operational Manual | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Disbursement Condition: Schedule 2, Section IV.B, paragraph 1(c) | Description :Notwithstanding the provisionsof Part A of this Section, no withdrawal shall be made: (c) under Category (3) until: the Borrower has declared a disaster,emergency or catastrophic event through the relevant national, Province- or Local Government-level or other authority, & the Bank &the Borrower have agreed in writing to address such disaster, emergency or catastrophic event under Part 4. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.B, paragraph 8 | Description :The Borrower, through the PMU, max.3 months after theEffective Date, issue instructions acceptable to the PMU & the Bank, to LGs defining time periods within which categories ofcomplaints/cases must be resolved, to whom they should be escalated if not resolved within such time periods & what theconsequences will be if such cases are not resolved or escalated in accordance with such instructions | Frequency :Yearly

title.narrative: Indicator Two: Satisfaction levels from beneficiaries regarding improved services and local governance
Indicator Three: Infrastructure built is at least 20% less expensive than that built by non community based approaches
Indicator One: Improved access to infrastructure, social, and/or economic services of the urban poor in participating kelurahan
Percentage of infrastructure works evaluated as of good quality
Percentage of the adult population voting in BKM elections at the neighborhood level
Percentage of kelurahan with revolving loan funds (RLFs) having a portfolio at risk (PAR) ratio ≥ 90 days of < 10%
Participation rate of women in planning and decision making meetings
Participation rate of poorest and vulnerable community members in planning and decision making meetings
Percentage of local governments provide required cost sharing
Percentage of provincial consultants providing timely & accurate data through MIS
Number of each type of infrastructure, economic, and social activities completed per year
Percentage of BKMs with completed annual financial audits
Indicator Four: At least 90% of complaints are resolved
